The paper discusses utilization-based schedulability test frameworks for real-time systems, which falls under the category of operating systems (cs.OS). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and analysis, which could potentially fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses scheduling in multiprocessor systems, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper mentions providing polynomial-time schedulability tests, which could potentially fall under programming languages (cs.PL).
